Enhancing Loan Management Efficiency for the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development (IBRD)

Overview:
This project aims to enhance loan management efficiency for the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development (IBRD) by analyzing historical loan data and identifying patterns behind loan cancellations. A scalable data pipeline is built using PySpark, Snowflake, and Azure Data Lake Storage to handle data ingestion, transformation, and storage. Through analytical queries and dashboards, the project provides insights into loan trends, and key borrowers, helping reduce cancellations and improve overall loan performance.

It implements an end-to-end data engineering pipeline using PySpark, Snowflake, and Power BI, following a Medallion Architecture (Bronze в†’ Silver в†’ Gold).

Architecture
The project follows a layered data architecture:

Bronze Layer Raw ingested data from World Bank Group (CSV files)

Silver Layer Cleaned and transformed data using PySpark:

Standardize column names
Cast numeric columns
Convert date columns
Handle missing values
Handle negative values
Handle duplicate records
Handle Text columns

Gold Layer Business-level aggregations:

Fact and dimension tables
KPI-ready datasets
Serving Layer Data is loaded into Snowflake and visualized using Power BI

Tech Stack
Azure - Cloud Platform
PySpark вЂ“ Distributed data processing
Snowflake вЂ“ Cloud data warehouse
Power BI вЂ“ Data visualization
Python вЂ“ Pipeline development

Data Pipeline

1. Data Ingestion Load raw CSV files into the Bronze layer

2. Data Cleaning (Silver Layer)

Remove null values
Standardize schema
Filter invalid records

3. Gold Layer Transformation

Create fact and dimension tables

- dim_customer
- dim_region
- dim_loan_type
- dim_date
- fact_loans

4. Data Warehousing

Load processed data into Snowflake Using Snowpipe
Create analytical views/Dynamic Tables

5. Visualization Build interactive dashboards in Power BI

Dashboard Insights
The dashboard provides:

Total Loans Analyzed, Total Loan Value, Loans Cancelled Amount, and Average Interest Rate
Loan Cancellation Trends
Top Loan Countries
Loans By Region
Top Projects
Loan Utilization

